         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>231</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>121</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>242</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>263</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2 #a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Aufgegangen sind die ausgezeichneten Kennzeichen: Es bebte die Erde, es regneten Perlen zusammen mit lieblichen Blumen [bzw. liebliche Perlen zusammen mit Blumen]</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The excellent signs have arisen: the earth has trembled, pearls have rained [down] together with lovely flowers [or: lovely pearls have rained [down] together with flowers]</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>121</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... das Wort "... m buddha" wird von(?) den Göttern ... gehört.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... the word "... m buddha" is heard by(?) the gods ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>255</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>286</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... sit down, you noble [men]!</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>404</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>140, 141</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the Purohita Brahmāyu, having raised both hands towards the sky ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the sun is rising. || ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1995"/><citedRange>64</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>240</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (No matter how many gods) ... from (all) directions revere (Brahmāvatī) with <hi>añjali</hi>-hands, you [pl.] too by day [and] (by night) ... him ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(No matter how many gods) … from (all) directions revere (Brahmāvatī) with añjali-hands, you [pl.] too by day [and] (by night) … him …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>287</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">MaitrHami 11, 3-4</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment contains part of the eleventh act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka; an Uy. parallel is MaitrHami XI, ca. 3a10-ca. 4a2. Lines b3-5 here correspond to MaitrHami XI, 3b4-b17; lines b6-7 to MaitrHami XI, 3b17-b29. See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>199-200</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">Fragment of a manuscript which includes A 251 - A 294 (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:gengetal2004a"/><citedRange>64-65</citedRange></bibl>). Lines a7-8 and b1-2 are lost.</note></p>
         </div>
